        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 4:02AM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 402 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Clear Lake National Wildlife Refuge, or 28 miles
northwest of Alturas, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Frequent lightning, winds in excess of 30 mph, and half
inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Drews Creek Recreation Site and Dog Lake Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
